FRONTEND:
To Create a React project template with Vite
  -npm create vite@latest my-vite-app --template react
  -Run npm create. Replace my-vite-app with an appropriate name for your application.
  -When it prompts you to select a framework, choose React.
  -When it prompts you to select a variant, choose JavaScript.

Navigate into your directory with cd <your-app-name>.
  -Install app dependencies with npm install
  -Start the development server with npm run dev
  -View your app by opening http://localhost:5173 in your browser.


BACKEND
  - Inside the project directory in your terminal, run the following command: npm init -y
  This command creates a package.json file in your project directory with default values.
  -Before you install Express, make sure your terminal is navigated to the root of your project directory. I
    Type the following command in your terminal and press Enter: npm install express

  PRISMA
  - Open your project directory in your terminal. Run the following command to install Prisma CLI as a development dependency: npm install prisma --save-dev
  - In your project directory, run: npx prisma init
    This command creates a new prisma folder with a schema.prisma file, outlining your database schema, and a .env file for environment variables.

IF YOU HAVE ALL THESE FILES SET UP, JUST TYPE IN node index.js to run the backend
